UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440768990081X
AB  - Taking certain aggregates of several continuously distributed welfare attributes as either the actual utility or the ‘observer's’ evaluation of individual welfare, Theil's information measures of inequality in the aggregates are derived and analyzed. The important special case where the joint distibution is the multivariate log-normal is developed as a point of departure. When this joint distribution is not the log-normal, simple approximate formulae for Theil'sindices are derived which are readily estimable. An attribute's incremental contribution to multidimensional inequality is derived and analysed.
ER  - 

